# DCS-OMM-Mods-and-Liveries

This repository contains custom **DCS World** Mods and Liveries configured for use with **OMM (Open Mod Manager)** or **OvGME**. It is organized to support easy activation/deactivation without conflicting with core game files. Ideal for squadrons, streamers, or solo pilots who want to quickly manage their mods and liveries.

---

## 📁 Repository Structure

DCS-OMM-Mods-and-Liveries/
├── Liveries/
│ ├── FA-18C_hornet/
│ │ └── VFA-192_BlackMajic/
│ └── F-14B/
│ └── VFA-192_Tomcat/
├── Mods/
│ ├── Sounds/
│ ├── Scripts/
│ └── Objects/
└── README.md


---

## 📦 How to Use with OMM / OvGME

1. Clone or download this repository.
2. Point your OMM mod folder to the root of this repository.
3. Enable/disable mods and liveries as needed through OMM.
4. Keep liveries in the correct path:

Saved Games\DCS.openbeta\Liveries<Aircraft_Type><Livery_Name>


---

## ✅ Recommended Mods

- [DCS SRS (Simple Radio)](https://github.com/ciribob/DCS-SimpleRadioStandalone)
- [DCS Kneeboard Builder](https://github.com/ronz84/DCS-Kneeboard-Builder)
- [DCS Utility Scripts (MOOSE, MIST, etc.)](https://github.com/FlightControl-Master/MOOSE)

